<paragraph id="355ED367FF8D8D423835FCFEFB1BFBB4" blockId="20.[827,1443,870,1048]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423835FCFEFC3EFCD2" box="[827,952,873,894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">Etymology:</emphasis>
From Japanese 
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423F70FCF1FB4EFCD2" bold="true" box="[1150,1224,870,894]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">さくら</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423FE2FCF1FAB0FCD2" bold="true" box="[1260,1334,870,894]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">サクĵ</emphasis>
(sakura), cherry blossoms, used here as a noun in apposition. Cherries are one of the most popular products from Valle del Jerte, where many cherry orchards are found. The flowering of cherry trees in springtime has become a famous and celebrated event.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="355ED367FF8D8D423835FBC3FC13FA54" blockId="20.[827,1443,1108,1528]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423835FBC3FC41FBC5" box="[827,967,1108,1129]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF8D8D423F95FBC3FA25FBC5" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[1179,1443,1108,1129]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Iberiarmadillidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423F95FBC3FA25FBC5" box="[1179,1443,1108,1129]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">Iberiarmadillidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characterized by rounded tubercles in pereonites, generally not elongated as in 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF8D8D423FE4FB05FAFFFB0B" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[1258,1401,1169,1191]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Iberiarmadillidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinicola">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423FE4FB05FAFFFB0B" box="[1258,1401,1169,1191]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">I. pinicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="F2E1A8E4FF8D8D423835FB27FBABFB69" authorityName="Recuero &amp; Rodríguez-Flores &amp; García-París" authorityYear="2022" box="[827,1069,1200,1221]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Iberiarmadillidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psammophilum">
<emphasis id="07950F75FF8D8D423835FB27FBABFB69" box="[827,1069,1200,1221]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1332">I. psammophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Lateralmost tubercles of pereonite 7 elongated, the frontal one longer than the caudal one. Tubercles in pleonite 5 equal to subequal in size. Pereonite 2 epimera with sinuous outer margin, pereonite 3 epimera with straight outer margin. Colour of epimera lighter than dorsal parts. Outer lobe of pleopod 1 endopod with almost straight margin. Pleopod 2 exopod with deeply concave outer/ distal margin; pleopod 2 endopod narrow, particularly in its distal half. Pleopod 4 exopod with concave distal margin.
</paragraph>
